This recipe is delicious, but a bit incomplete. You should serve with shredded Oaxaca and Crema Mexicana for authenticity. If you can't get those, Mozzarella will substitute, and natural sour cream thinned with milk. Also, it tastes better if you'll save a chicken carcass and cook it off for your own stock instead of canned. Part of the "bland" people are getting is from bought stock or broth vs homemade.

