Rating: 4
My wife is from San Antonio, TX, and grew up with torilla soup (there is a terrific little restaurant down there, "Twin Sisters," which does a nice version). I have made this recipe a few times, and would consider it excellent. I often make a few changes, which add maybe a little time, but result in a terrific dish. Rather than cooking the chicken into the broth, I salted/peppered/olive oiled a couple of boneless chicken breasts and baked them ahead of time. When cooled, I hand-shredded them in 1/2" chunks. Mexican stewed tomatoes are not readily available here, and Rotels are too tangy, so I used Italian stewed tomatoes, crushed by hand. Also, I just used all stock rather than 1/2 stock, 1/2 water. Finally, we also fried the tortilla strips in canola and drained them thoroughly. The strips tend to curl a little, which is neat for the texture. Garnish with avocado.

