Rating: 3
I largely followed the advice of one previous reviewer and changed the recipe like this: I first sauteed onions and garlic, then added diced chicken tenderloin meat and browned that for a couple minutes, removed the chicken and set aside, then added a 14 oz can of tomatoes with jalapenos to the pot, then the cumin, then the chicken broth and water. I added some crushed (store bought) tortilla chips at that point and let them dissolve into the broth as the soup simmered. After about a half hour of simmering, I added the chicken back to the soup to finish cooking along with a can of corn (drained) and a can of black beans (drained), then finished it off with lime juice and cilantro. The first night I used avocados as a topping along with cheese, scallions, and tortilla chips, but I felt the flavor of the avocados got lost. The next night, I added rice to the soup to make the leftovers stretch, and this was a very nice addition (next time I will add the rice straight away), and topped it with tortilla chips, jack cheese, and scallions. Wonderful!

