Rating: 3
Excellent tortilla soup with a few minor tweaks. Was thinking to add oregano to the recipe but am glad that I didn't. For ease in preparation I used store bought tortilla strips that were baked, and a lemon herb baked chicken from the local market's deli that I shredded. I prepared 1.5 times the recipe to have leftovers for next day lunch. Sub'd 14 oz. can of whole plum tomatoes that I pulsed in the food processor. Equal to 2t. of cumin, and 4T. of lime juice. Sauteed 1 medium diced onion along with the garlic (always more garlic), added tomatoes, and small can of diced green chilies, then cumin. Added broth and 1/2c. of crushed tortilla chips. Simmered until chips were absorbed into the broth then added chicken, 1 can of corn, and 1 can of drained and rinsed black beans. Lastly added lime juice. Ladled soup into bowls and topped with crushed tortilla strips then garnished with chopped cilantro, green onions, diced avocado, grated jack cheese, and a dollop of sour cream. Served with cucumber slices dressed simply with lime juice and a sprinkle of chili powder. Chili's enchilada soup pales in comparison to this recipe. Family LOVED this soup!

