This is a good, easy starting point; it's much better with some doctoring. I added a whole 14-oz. can of stewed tomatoes and pureed them slightly with a hand blender to give the soup more body. I added a minced fresh jalapeno pepper (two would have been even better); diced the chicken breast instead of cutting into strips; and topped the soup with Jack cheese. Next time I'd add a handful of the tortilla strips to the soup and let them cook down to release some starch (for thickness), and increase the lime from 2 to 3 tbsp. I agree with other reviewers who say it needs corn or beans or both to round it out. Also, seasoned roasted chicken would give it better flavor than plain.

