Rating: 3
I have made this recipe dozens of times over the last two years. This has been a guest pleaser and highly sought after soup since I made some changes. To make this a four fork soup I changed the following. Use pork roast instead of chicken. Throw it in a slow cooker over nite (I've also roasted it in the oven in a clay pot) then let in cool and shred it by hand (remove all fat as shredding). Add the juice from the slow cooker or oven roasting in the soup later. Roast a couple pablano peppers, peel the skin, dice up, and add to soup. Double or triple the lime juice. Add an ounce of fresh squeezed OJ. I use a couple large cans of Rotel dice tomatoes. Skip the chips. This has been a guest pleaser and highly sought after soup since I made the changes. For the absolute best results, use homemade chicken broth. If you need a large batch, just shred the chicken from the broth preparation and add it to the pork. This freezes very well.

