Rating: 3
While visiting San Antonio I had the most delicious tortilla soup. I was anxious to recreate it and based on the reviews of others I selected this recipe -- and it was delicious! I toasted different flavoured flour tortillas (regular, basil and sun-dried tomato) to add colour and added some cheese to the bowl to serve. It was wonderful!

Rating: 4
I first found this recipe about a year ago. It is, without a doubt, the best tortilla soup in the world. I tried many restaurants here in Houston...but there is no comparison. I think it is the fresh lime that does it, along with the cilantro. IT is beyond compare.

Rating: 4
I've tried lots of tortilla soups but there was always something I didn't care for in them. I couldn't put my finger on it till I tried this recipe. The others had too much of a tomato base and not enough or no cilantro. This broth was clear and YUMMY! Sometimes I add a handful of Minute rice for added texture and to make it a little more filling. I also sprinkle a small amount of three cheese mexican blend on top.